cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on learning program semantics using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as Gated Graph Neural Networks and TreeLSTM, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the models' ability to detect deeper semantic properties of a program, which is related to computer security (cs.CR).
